The paper deals with the problem of private information retrieval, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The focus is on the storage constrained scenario, which involves constraints on the storage capacity of the databases, making it relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), distributed computing (cs.DC), and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of coding techniques, which is relevant to the sub-category of coding theory (cs.CC).
